        <div class="guidelinesColumns">
            <div fxFlex="360px">
                <p>Checkboxes allow the user to select multiple options from a set. If you have multiple options appearing in
                    a list, you can preserve space by using checkboxes instead of on/off switches. If you have a single option,
                    avoid using a checkbox and use an on/off switch instead.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>A checkbox can either be a primary action or a secondary action.</li>
                    <li>Type: primary action/state</li>
                    <li>Desktop checkboxes should appear only on hover and focus.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div fxFlex>
                <img src="assets/images/checkbox/components_listcontrols_checkbox1.png" width="760" />
                <p>The checkbox is the primary action and the state indicator for the list item.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

